#: ../../export_tools/twitter_export.rst:18
msgid "This tool allows the user to upload photos to the Twitter social network."
msgstr ""

#: ../../export_tools/twitter_export.rst:20
msgid "`Twitter <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Twitter>`_  is an online social media and social networking service. Users can send and respond publicly or privately texts, images and videos known as *tweets*. Publication are publicly visible by default, but senders can restrict message delivery to only their followers. Twitter supports photo-sharing service that enables users to upload a photo and attach it to a tweet."
msgstr ""

#: ../../export_tools/twitter_export.rst:22
msgid "The tool can be used to upload and tweet a selection of images from your collection to the remote Twitter server using the Internet."
msgstr ""

#: ../../export_tools/twitter_export.rst:24
msgid "When accessing the tool for the first time by the :menuselection:`Export --> Export to Twitter` menu entry, you are taken through the process of obtaining a token which is used for authentication purposes. The following dialog will popup and a browser window will be launched you will log in to Twitter:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../export_tools/twitter_export.rst:30
msgid "The Twitter Authorize Dialog"
msgstr ""

#: ../../export_tools/twitter_export.rst:32
msgid "After successful sign-up digiKam will be allowed to send photos to the Twitter website. You will be presented with the following page:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../export_tools/twitter_export.rst:38
msgid "The Twitter Login Dialog"
msgstr ""

#: ../../export_tools/twitter_export.rst:40
msgid "Then, simply authorize application and close the web browser. Return to the host application dialog, you will see the interface used to upload photos to Twitter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../export_tools/twitter_export.rst:46
msgid "The Twitter Export Tool Dialog"
msgstr ""

#: ../../export_tools/twitter_export.rst:48
msgid "By default, the tool proposes to export the currently selected items from the icon-view. The **+** Photos button can be used to append more items on the list."
msgstr ""

#: ../../export_tools/twitter_export.rst:50
msgid "If the **Resize photos before uploading** option is selected, the photos will be resized before transferring to Twitter. The values will be read from the **JPEG quality** and **Maximum Dimension** settings, which can be used to adjust the maximum height and the compression. The width calculation will be done so as to have the aspect ratio conserved."
msgstr ""

#: ../../export_tools/twitter_export.rst:56
msgid "The Twitter Export Uploading in Progress"
msgstr ""

#: ../../export_tools/twitter_export.rst:58
msgid "Press **Start Upload** button to transfer items. You can click on the **Close** button to abort the uploading of photos."
msgstr ""

#: ../../export_tools/twitter_export.rst:60
msgid "Finally, you can view the uploaded photos by visiting the Twitter website."
msgstr ""

